member.name: P:Gremlin.Net.Driver.ConnectionPoolSettings.ReconnectionAttempts
member.summary: Gets or sets the number of attempts to get an open connection from the pool to submit a request.
member.exception: The number of attempts specified is less than zero.
member.remarks:
The driver always tries to reconnect to a server in the background after it has noticed that a connection is dead. This setting only specifies how often the driver will retry to get an open connection from its pool when no open connection is available to submit a request. These retries give the driver time to establish new connections to the server that might have been unavailable temporarily or that might have closed the connections, e.g., because they were idle for some time.
The default value is 4. A is thrown if the server can still not be reached after this many retry attempts.
Setting this to zero means that the exception is thrown immediately when no open connection is available to submit a request. The driver will however still try to reconnect to the server in the background for subsequent requests.

member.name: P:Gremlin.Net.Driver.ConnectionPoolSettings.ReconnectionBaseDelay
member.summary: Gets or sets the base delay used for the exponential backoff for the reconnection attempts.
member.exception: The specified delay is negative or zero.
member.remarks:
The driver employs an exponential backoff strategy that uses this base delay for its reconnection attempts. With a base delay of 100 ms for example, retries happen after 100 ms, 200 ms, 400 ms, 800 ms, and so on, assuming that enough are configured.
The default value is 1 second.
